> Comments are better at explaining things than cryptic variable names anyhow.<p>I&#x27;d pick<p><pre><code>  const DEFAULT_FONT_SIZE = 42;

  // ... lots of code in the same file

  var font = new Font(DEFAULT_FONT_SIZE)
</code></pre>
over<p><pre><code>  // 42 is the default font size
  var font = new Font(42);
</code></pre>
any time.<p>Two reasons: version 2 encourages others to copy-paste out of laziness, and it does not resist refactoring very well.
